{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}} {{Use British English|date=February 2017}} The '''Lands Valuation Appeal Court''' is a Scottish [[Scottish civil court|civil court]], composed of 3 [[Court of Session]] judges. It hears cases where the decision of a local Valuation Appeal Committee is disputed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/Government/local-government/17999/11199/brief-guide/valuationappeal|title=Non-Domestic Rates - Valuation Appeals|accessdate = 16 June 2013}}</ref>
