{{Infobox Website | name = Safe Creative | logo = Logo safe creative.png | favicon = | caption = | url = https://safecreative.org | commercial = Yes | type = [[copyright registration]] service | registration = free and paid | owner = | author = | launch date = | current status = active | revenue = }}
'''Safe Creative''' is a digital copyright registration service to show evidence of copyright registration for the owners of the creative material in the case of [[plagiarism]] or misuse of copyrighted materials.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.plagiarismtoday.com/2009/02/11/safe-creative-a-good-start-to-protecting-works/ |title=Safe Creative: A Good Start to Protecting Works |accessdate=November 29, 2011 |date=February 11, 2009 |first=Jonathan |last=Bailey}}</ref>
==Main Features of Safe Creative== * Valid registration for any [[copyright]] option ([[copyleft]] or "[[all rights reserved]])" * Authorship evidence based on: deposit of the work, redundant [[hash function|hash]]; ([[MD5]], [[SHA-1]], [[SHA512]]) from the deposited file, redundant timestamp of the time and hour or registration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wipo.int/multimedia-video/en/meetings/wipo_cr_doc_ge_11/adsuara_eng_13oct2011.mp3 |title=Safe Creative at WIPO meeting on Private Online Registries|accessdate=February 23, 2012|publisher =WIPO}}</ref> * Open [[API]] interface for the recording of authorship claims and queries from external systems. * Technological framework implemented: [[Semantic Copyright]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://labs.creativecommons.org/2010/09/02/semantic-copyright-and-cc-rel/ | title="Semantic Copyright" and CC REL |accessdate=November 29, 2011 |last=Creative Commons |date=September 2, 2010 }}</ref> * Automatic [[RSS]] channel registration. * Direct author licensing system. * Registration at the [[United States Copyright Office]] * Movies and TV formats registration with collaboration of official Spanish movies and TV producers [[copyright]] [[collecting society]] [[EGEDA]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rtve.es/noticias/20121211/nace-primer-registro-online-obras-audiovisuales-grabaciones-guiones/585284.shtml |title=Nace el primer registro "online" de obras audiovisuales, grabaciones y guiones|accessdate=April 12, 2013|publisher =RTVE.es}}</ref> and Spain National Registrars<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tecnologia.elpais.com/tecnologia/2012/12/11/actualidad/1355240573_467381.html |title=Acuerdo de Creative Safe con los autores|accessdate=April 12, 2013|publisher =http://tecnologia.elpais.com}}</ref>
==Reception== Plagiarism Today praised the website for having a "rich API" and being "feature rich", but stated that the website could be "confusing and intimidating to use" for those unexperienced with copyrighting.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.plagiarismtoday.com/2009/11/20/5-copyright-verification-services-compared/ |title=5 Copyright Verification Services Compared |date=November 20, 2009}}</ref>
Sites such as Jamendo<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.jamendo.com/2009/09/02/artists-protect-your-music-with-safecreative/ |title=Artists, protect your music with Safe Creative! |accessdate=November 19, 2011 |publisher =Jamendo }}</ref> , dibujando.net,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dibujando.net/noticia/dibujandonet-firma-un-acuerdo-colaboracion-con-safe-creative-2808 |title=Dibujando.net firma un acuerdo de colaboración con Safe Creative |accessdate=June 19, 2011 |publisher =dibujando.net }}</ref> talentyArt<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.talentyart.com/actualidad/talentyart-se-covierte-en-partner-de-safe-creative |title=TalentyArt se convierte en Partner de Safe Creative |accessdate=June 21, 2011 |last=Saavedra |first=Matilde |publisher =TalentyArt }}</ref> and VirtualGallery have partnered with Safe Creative to protect the output of their users via copyright.
Authors of [[WIPO]] survey on private registries<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wipo.int/export/sites/www/meetings/en/2011/wipo_cr_doc_ge_11/pdf/survey_private_crdocystems.pdf |title=WIPO Survey on Private Registries |accessdate=November 14, 2012|publisher =WIPO}}</ref> states that as long as it is possible to testify about the technical characteristics of online registries, there is no reason to doubt about the validity of the generated evidence. Also they consider that one of the main advantages of a private registry based on transparency, such as Safe Creative, when comparing them with public official registries is to make copyright information quickly available to the public and those interested in reaching collaborations and partnerships.
